            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I think we agree that a context-menu which can be controlled with the mouse can be useful. My only concern is if it couldn't be modified by the user. Sure it could have a default configuration but I think there would be many usecase which the neovim-devs can not foresee and shouldn't be responsible for. For example plugin-developers for file-explorers like NERDTree maybe would want to use such a context-menu. It would be a huge waste of potential if only the neovim-devs would have control over the context-menu and not the users, plugin-developers and the whole community.\r\n\r\nMy point is it shouldn't be limited to a set of hardcoded features but rather be customizable and maybe be deployed with a default configuration.",
